    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-12T02:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-12T02:35:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9131/171: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-12T11:00:00+03:25"
                            >May 12, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>150. Department’s No. 111, May 2, 11 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m.</hi>] I am
                    informed by the Under Secretary of Finance that Saleh has been instructed to
                    inform Department that the Iranian Government is prepared in principle to
                    consider reductions in duties or supplementary charges and bindings of duties on
                    products of interest to the United States. The agreement would however be
                    subject to ratification by Medjliss. Saleh has been instructed to submit a list
                    of articles on which United States requests reductions or bindings.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
